---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="A journey through microbiome informatics, open source, and AI for Science"
	pubDate={new Date('2026-03-13')}
>
	<div class="about-content">
		<p class="lead">
			Hi, I'm <strong>alienzj</strong> — a researcher and bioinformatics engineer passionate about
			<strong>Microbiome Informatics</strong>. I dedicate my work to building robust, reproducible
			tools that help scientists understand the complex world of microbial communities.
		</p>

		<h2>🔬 My Research Journey</h2>
		<p>
			My work centers on <strong>metagenomics</strong> — the study of genetic material recovered
			directly from environmental samples. I focus on:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Metagenome-Assembled Genomes (MAGs)</strong> — Recovering and analyzing microbial
				genomes from complex communities without cultivation</li>
			<li><strong>Workflow Automation</strong> — Building reproducible pipelines using Snakemake,
				Nextflow, and containerization technologies</li>
			<li><strong>Microbiome Data Mining</strong> — Statistical analysis and ecological interpretation
				of multi-omics data</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>🏢 OhMeta</h2>
		<p>
			I co-founded <a href="https://github.com/ohmeta" target="_blank" rel="noopener">OhMeta</a>,
			an organization dedicated to developing open-source tools for microbiome research. Our mission
			is to make metagenomics analysis more accessible and robust for researchers worldwide.
		</p>
		<p>Key projects include:</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>metapi</strong> — A general metagenomics data mining system</li>
			<li><strong>quantpi</strong> — Microbiome profiling pipeline</li>
			<li><strong>rnapi</strong> — RNA-seq analysis pipeline</li>
			<li><strong>qiimepi</strong> — Snakemake implementation of QIIME2</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>🤖 AI for Science</h2>
		<p>
			I'm deeply interested in how <strong>AI and LLMs</strong> can transform scientific research.
			My explorations include:
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>Building autonomous agents for literature review and data analysis</li>
			<li>LLM-powered workflow orchestration for reproducible research</li>
			<li>Intelligent tools that augment human scientific discovery</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>🌱 Personal Philosophy</h2>
		<p>
			As an <strong>INFJ</strong> personality type, I approach research with:
		</p>
		<ul class="infj-traits">
			<li><strong>Idealism</strong> — Believing that open science can make the world better</li>
			<li><strong>Empathy</strong> — Designing tools with the end user's experience in mind</li>
			<li><strong>Depth</strong> — Preferring meaningful contributions over superficial metrics</li>
			<li><strong>Integration</strong> — Seeing connections between disparate fields and ideas</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>🏠 Life Beyond Code</h2>
		<p>When I'm not analyzing genomes or writing pipelines, you can find me:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>🚴 <strong>Cycling</strong> — Exploring roads and trails, finding balance between screen time and nature</li>
			<li>🖥️ <strong>HomeLab</strong> — Running self-hosted services on Proxmox and TrueNAS</li>
			<li>🎮 <strong>Indie Games</strong> — Playing thoughtful, narrative-driven experiences</li>
			<li>🏀 <strong>Basketball</strong> — Staying active and healthy</li>
		</ul>

		<blockquote>
			<p>"MAGs lives matter" 🦀</p>
			<p class="quote-attribution">— A reminder that even the smallest organisms deserve attention, and that diversity (microbial and otherwise) is what makes our world rich and resilient.</p>
		</blockquote>

		<h2>📬 Connect</h2>
		<p>
			I'm always open to discussing collaborations, new ideas, or just chatting about
			microbiomes and AI. Feel free to reach out via
			<a href="https://github.com/alienzj" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a> or
			visit my website at <a href="https://alienzj.tech" target="_blank" rel="noopener">alienzj.tech</a>.
		</p>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.about-content {
		max-width: 720px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.lead {
		font-size: 1.15em;
		line-height: 1.8;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
	}

	.about-content h2 {
		margin-top: 2.5em;
		margin-bottom: 1em;
	}

	.about-content ul {
		margin-bottom: 1.5em;
	}

	.about-content li {
		margin-bottom: 0.75em;
		line-height: 1.7;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
	}

	.infj-traits li {
		padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
		background: rgba(var(--gray-light), 30%);
		border-radius: 6px;
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
		transition: background 0.2s ease;
	}

	.infj-traits li:hover {
		background: rgba(var(--gray-light), 50%);
	}

	.infj-traits strong {
		color: var(--accent);
	}

	.quote-attribution {
		font-size: 0.9em;
		font-style: italic;
		margin-top: 1em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
	}

	.quote-attribution::before {
		content: "— ";
	}

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.lead {
			font-size: 1.05em;
		}
	}
</style>
